{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":562,"text":"I'm going to talk about the strategizing brain."},{"time":2815,"text":"We're going to use an unusual combination of tools"},{"time":5053,"text":"from game theory and neuroscience"},{"time":7066,"text":"to understand how people interact socially when value is on the line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10033,"text":"So game theory is a branch of, originally, applied mathematics,"},{"time":14004,"text":"used mostly in economics and political science, a little bit in biology,"},{"time":16990,"text":"that gives us a mathematical taxonomy of social life"},{"time":20279,"text":"and it predicts what people are likely to do"},{"time":22410,"text":"and believe others will do"},{"time":23604,"text":"in cases where everyone's actions affect everyone else."},{"time":26994,"text":"That's a lot of things: competition, cooperation, bargaining,"},{"time":30472,"text":"games like hide-and-seek, and poker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33763,"text":"Here's a simple game to get us started."},{"time":36002,"text":"Everyone chooses a number from zero to 100,"},{"time":38164,"text":"we're going to compute the average of those numbers,"},{"time":40610,"text":"and whoever's closest to two-thirds of the average wins a fixed prize."},{"time":44804,"text":"So you want to be a little bit below the average number,"},{"time":47073,"text":"but not too far below, and everyone else wants to be"},{"time":49309,"text":"a little bit below the average number as well."},{"time":51254,"text":"Think about what you might pick."},{"time":53833,"text":"As you're thinking, this is a toy model of something like"},{"time":57104,"text":"selling in the stock market during a rising market. Right?"},{"time":59916,"text":"You don't want to sell too early, because you miss out on profits,"},{"time":62141,"text":"but you don't want to wait too late"},{"time":64321,"text":"to when everyone else sells, triggering a crash."},{"time":66722,"text":"You want to be a little bit ahead of the competition, but not too far ahead."},{"time":69601,"text":"Okay, here's two theories about how people might think about this,"},{"time":73214,"text":"and then we'll see some data."},{"time":74610,"text":"Some of these will sound familiar because you probably are"},{"time":76801,"text":"thinking that way. I'm using my brain theory to see."},{"time":80600,"text":"A lot of people say, \"I really don't know what people are going to pick,"},{"time":83710,"text":"so I think the average will be 50.\""},{"time":85383,"text":"They're not being really strategic at all."},{"time":87294,"text":"\"And I'll pick two-thirds of 50. That's 33.\" That's a start."},{"time":90646,"text":"Other people who are a little more sophisticated,"},{"time":92538,"text":"using more working memory,"},{"time":94014,"text":"say, \"I think people will pick 33 because they're going to pick a response to 50,"},{"time":97918,"text":"and so I'll pick 22, which is two-thirds of 33.\""},{"time":100886,"text":"They're doing one extra step of thinking, two steps."},{"time":103365,"text":"That's better. And of course, in principle,"},{"time":105982,"text":"you could do three, four or more,"},{"time":107809,"text":"but it starts to get very difficult."},{"time":109678,"text":"Just like in language and other domains, we know that it's hard for people to parse"},{"time":112270,"text":"very complex sentences with a kind of recursive structure."},{"time":115904,"text":"This is called a cognitive hierarchy theory, by the way."},{"time":117638,"text":"It's something that I've worked on and a few other people,"},{"time":120194,"text":"and it indicates a kind of hierarchy along with"},{"time":122414,"text":"some assumptions about how many people stop at different steps"},{"time":124668,"text":"and how the steps of thinking are affected"},{"time":126552,"text":"by lots of interesting variables and variant people, as we'll see in a minute."},{"time":130248,"text":"A very different theory, a much more popular one, and an older one,"},{"time":133634,"text":"due largely to John Nash of \"A Beautiful Mind\" fame,"},{"time":137174,"text":"is what's called equilibrium analysis."},{"time":139414,"text":"So if you've ever taken a game theory course at any level,"},{"time":141868,"text":"you will have learned a little bit about this."},{"time":143581,"text":"An equilibrium is a mathematical state in which everybody"},{"time":146436,"text":"has figured out exactly what everyone else will do."},{"time":148885,"text":"It is a very useful concept, but behaviorally,"},{"time":150892,"text":"it may not exactly explain what people do"},{"time":152895,"text":"the first time they play these types of economic games"},{"time":155630,"text":"or in situations in the outside world."},{"time":157963,"text":"In this case, the equilibrium makes a very bold prediction,"},{"time":160301,"text":"which is everyone wants to be below everyone else,"},{"time":163161,"text":"therefore they'll play zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165452,"text":"Let's see what happens. This experiment's been done many, many times."},{"time":168461,"text":"Some of the earliest ones were done in the '90s"},{"time":170344,"text":"by me and Rosemarie Nagel and others."},{"time":172989,"text":"This is a beautiful data set of 9,000 people who wrote in"},{"time":175974,"text":"to three newspapers and magazines that had a contest."},{"time":178854,"text":"The contest said, send in your numbers"},{"time":180668,"text":"and whoever is close to two-thirds of the average will win a big prize."},{"time":183823,"text":"And as you can see, there's so much data here, you can see the spikes very visibly."},{"time":186911,"text":"There's a spike at 33. Those are people doing one step."},{"time":190292,"text":"There is another spike visible at 22."},{"time":192789,"text":"And notice, by the way, that most people pick numbers right around there."},{"time":195081,"text":"They don't necessarily pick exactly 33 and 22."},{"time":197591,"text":"There's something a little bit noisy around it."},{"time":199647,"text":"But you can see those spikes, and they're there."},{"time":201125,"text":"There's another group of people who seem to have"},{"time":202835,"text":"a firm grip on equilibrium analysis,"},{"time":204910,"text":"because they're picking zero or one."},{"time":207305,"text":"But they lose, right?"},{"time":209394,"text":"Because picking a number that low is actually a bad choice"},{"time":212586,"text":"if other people aren't doing equilibrium analysis as well."},{"time":215406,"text":"So they're smart, but poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217518,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219606,"text":"Where are these things happening in the brain?"},{"time":221575,"text":"One study by Coricelli and Nagel gives a really sharp, interesting answer."},{"time":225450,"text":"So they had people play this game"},{"time":226958,"text":"while they were being scanned in an fMRI,"},{"time":229175,"text":"and two conditions: in some trials,"},{"time":231446,"text":"they're told you're playing another person"},{"time":232961,"text":"who's playing right now and we're going to match up"},{"time":234549,"text":"your behavior at the end and pay you if you win."},{"time":236753,"text":"In the other trials, they're told, you're playing a computer."},{"time":238731,"text":"They're just choosing randomly."},{"time":240365,"text":"So what you see here is a subtraction"},{"time":242442,"text":"of areas in which there's more brain activity"},{"time":245192,"text":"when you're playing people compared to playing the computer."},{"time":248168,"text":"And you see activity in some regions we've seen today,"},{"time":250159,"text":"medial prefrontal cortex, dorsomedial, however, up here,"},{"time":253396,"text":"ventromedial prefrontal cortex,"},{"time":255247,"text":"anterior cingulate, an area that's involved"},{"time":256601,"text":"in lots of types of conflict resolution, like if you're playing \"Simon Says,\""},{"time":260238,"text":"and also the right and left temporoparietal junction."},{"time":264052,"text":"And these are all areas which are fairly reliably known"},{"time":266518,"text":"to be part of what's called a \"theory of mind\" circuit,"},{"time":268839,"text":"or \"mentalizing circuit.\""},{"time":270740,"text":"That is, it's a circuit that's used to imagine what other people might do."},{"time":274118,"text":"So these were some of the first studies to see this"},{"time":276358,"text":"tied in to game theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278391,"text":"What happens with these one- and two-step types?"},{"time":280631,"text":"So we classify people by what they picked,"},{"time":282702,"text":"and then we look at the difference between"},{"time":284369,"text":"playing humans versus playing computers,"},{"time":286344,"text":"which brain areas are differentially active."},{"time":288235,"text":"On the top you see the one-step players."},{"time":289987,"text":"There's almost no difference."},{"time":291507,"text":"The reason is, they're treating other people like a computer, and the brain is too."},{"time":294447,"text":"The bottom players, you see all the activity in dorsomedial PFC."},{"time":298588,"text":"So we know that those two-step players are doing something differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300639,"text":"Now if you were to step back and say, \"What can we do with this information?\""},{"time":303735,"text":"you might be able to look at brain activity and say,"},{"time":305556,"text":"\"This person's going to be a good poker player,\""},{"time":307055,"text":"or, \"This person's socially naive,\""},{"time":308984,"text":"and we might also be able to study things"},{"time":310262,"text":"like development of adolescent brains"},{"time":311860,"text":"once we have an idea of where this circuitry exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315214,"text":"Okay. Get ready."},{"time":317826,"text":"I'm saving you some brain activity,"},{"time":319949,"text":"because you don't need to use your hair detector cells."},{"time":322759,"text":"You should use those cells to think carefully about this game."},{"time":325647,"text":"This is a bargaining game."},{"time":327582,"text":"Two players who are being scanned using EEG electrodes"},{"time":330138,"text":"are going to bargain over one to six dollars."},{"time":333015,"text":"If they can do it in 10 seconds, they're going to actually earn that money."},{"time":335679,"text":"If 10 seconds goes by and they haven't made a deal, they get nothing."},{"time":338719,"text":"That's kind of a mistake together."},{"time":340402,"text":"The twist is that one player, on the left,"},{"time":343219,"text":"is informed about how much on each trial there is."},{"time":345907,"text":"They play lots of trials with different amounts each time."},{"time":348139,"text":"In this case, they know there's four dollars."},{"time":350380,"text":"The uninformed player doesn't know,"},{"time":352257,"text":"but they know that the informed player knows."},{"time":354311,"text":"So the uninformed player's challenge is to say,"},{"time":356370,"text":"\"Is this guy really being fair"},{"time":357840,"text":"or are they giving me a very low offer"},{"time":359694,"text":"in order to get me to think that there's only one or two dollars available to split?\""},{"time":362772,"text":"in which case they might reject it and not come to a deal."},{"time":365926,"text":"So there's some tension here between trying to get the most money"},{"time":368876,"text":"but trying to goad the other player into giving you more."},{"time":371449,"text":"And the way they bargain is to point on a number line"},{"time":373779,"text":"that goes from zero to six dollars,"},{"time":375585,"text":"and they're bargaining over how much the uninformed player gets,"},{"time":378563,"text":"and the informed player's going to get the rest."},{"time":380148,"text":"So this is like a management-labor negotiation"},{"time":382723,"text":"in which the workers don't know how much profits"},{"time":385456,"text":"the privately held company has, right,"},{"time":388123,"text":"and they want to maybe hold out for more money,"},{"time":390491,"text":"but the company might want to create the impression"},{"time":392327,"text":"that there's very little to split: \"I'm giving you the most that I can.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":395259,"text":"First some behavior. So a bunch of the subject pairs, they play face to face."},{"time":399490,"text":"We have some other data where they play across computers."},{"time":401326,"text":"That's an interesting difference, as you might imagine."},{"time":403064,"text":"But a bunch of the face-to-face pairs"},{"time":405266,"text":"agree to divide the money evenly every single time."},{"time":408959,"text":"Boring. It's just not interesting neurally."},{"time":411865,"text":"It's good for them. They make a lot of money."},{"time":414379,"text":"But we're interested in, can we say something about"},{"time":417051,"text":"when disagreements occur versus don't occur?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419587,"text":"So this is the other group of subjects who often disagree."},{"time":421944,"text":"So they have a chance of -- they bicker and disagree"},{"time":424712,"text":"and end up with less money."},{"time":426019,"text":"They might be eligible to be on \"Real Housewives,\" the TV show."},{"time":429936,"text":"You see on the left,"},{"time":431872,"text":"when the amount to divide is one, two or three dollars,"},{"time":434536,"text":"they disagree about half the time,"},{"time":436184,"text":"and when the amount is four, five, six, they agree quite often."},{"time":438376,"text":"This turns out to be something that's predicted"},{"time":440250,"text":"by a very complicated type of game theory"},{"time":442454,"text":"you should come to graduate school at CalTech and learn about."},{"time":445263,"text":"It's a little too complicated to explain right now,"},{"time":447435,"text":"but the theory tells you that this shape kind of should occur."},{"time":450851,"text":"Your intuition might tell you that too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453067,"text":"Now I'm going to show you the results from the EEG recording."},{"time":455307,"text":"Very complicated. The right brain schematic"},{"time":457660,"text":"is the uninformed person, and the left is the informed."},{"time":460523,"text":"Remember that we scanned both brains at the same time,"},{"time":463323,"text":"so we can ask about time-synced activity"},{"time":465715,"text":"in similar or different areas simultaneously,"},{"time":468939,"text":"just like if you wanted to study a conversation"},{"time":471203,"text":"and you were scanning two people talking to each other"},{"time":473139,"text":"and you'd expect common activity in language regions"},{"time":475499,"text":"when they're actually kind of listening and communicating."},{"time":477884,"text":"So the arrows connect regions that are active at the same time,"},{"time":481811,"text":"and the direction of the arrows flows"},{"time":483851,"text":"from the region that's active first in time,"},{"time":486331,"text":"and the arrowhead goes to the region that's active later."},{"time":489899,"text":"So in this case, if you look carefully,"},{"time":492115,"text":"most of the arrows flow from right to left."},{"time":493972,"text":"That is, it looks as if the uninformed brain activity"},{"time":497252,"text":"is happening first,"},{"time":499211,"text":"and then it's followed by activity in the informed brain."},{"time":502726,"text":"And by the way, these were trials where their deals were made."},{"time":506418,"text":"This is from the first two seconds."},{"time":508198,"text":"We haven't finished analyzing this data,"},{"time":510178,"text":"so we're still peeking in, but the hope is"},{"time":512078,"text":"that we can say something in the first couple of seconds"},{"time":514642,"text":"about whether they'll make a deal or not,"},{"time":516365,"text":"which could be very useful in thinking about avoiding litigation"},{"time":518408,"text":"and ugly divorces and things like that."},{"time":520336,"text":"Those are all cases in which a lot of value is lost"},{"time":523219,"text":"by delay and strikes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526195,"text":"Here's the case where the disagreements occur."},{"time":528225,"text":"You can see it looks different than the one before."},{"time":530398,"text":"There's a lot more arrows."},{"time":532647,"text":"That means that the brains are synced up"},{"time":534158,"text":"more closely in terms of simultaneous activity,"},{"time":536710,"text":"and the arrows flow clearly from left to right."},{"time":538720,"text":"That is, the informed brain seems to be deciding,"},{"time":540962,"text":"\"We're probably not going to make a deal here.\""},{"time":543250,"text":"And then later there's activity in the uninformed brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546475,"text":"Next I'm going to introduce you to some relatives."},{"time":548978,"text":"They're hairy, smelly, fast and strong."},{"time":551239,"text":"You might be thinking back to your last Thanksgiving."},{"time":554429,"text":"Maybe if you had a chimpanzee with you."},{"time":557122,"text":"Charles Darwin and I and you broke off from the family tree"},{"time":560583,"text":"from chimpanzees about five million years ago."},{"time":562842,"text":"They're still our closest genetic kin."},{"time":564810,"text":"We share 98.8 percent of the genes."},{"time":566547,"text":"We share more genes with them than zebras do with horses."},{"time":569347,"text":"And we're also their closest cousin."},{"time":571064,"text":"They have more genetic relation to us than to gorillas."},{"time":574066,"text":"So how humans and chimpanzees behave differently"},{"time":576594,"text":"might tell us a lot about brain evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579049,"text":"So this is an amazing memory test"},{"time":581650,"text":"from Nagoya, Japan, Primate Research Institute,"},{"time":584466,"text":"where they've done a lot of this research."},{"time":586244,"text":"This goes back quite a ways. They're interested in working memory."},{"time":588584,"text":"The chimp is going to see, watch carefully,"},{"time":590356,"text":"they're going to see 200 milliseconds' exposure"},{"time":592558,"text":"— that's fast, that's eight movie frames —"},{"time":594552,"text":"of numbers one, two, three, four, five."},{"time":596503,"text":"Then they disappear and they're replaced by squares,"},{"time":598501,"text":"and they have to press the squares"},{"time":600256,"text":"that correspond to the numbers from low to high"},{"time":602577,"text":"to get an apple reward."},{"time":603916,"text":"Let's see how they can do it."},{"time":616391,"text":"This is a young chimp. The young ones"},{"time":617884,"text":"are better than the old ones, just like humans."},{"time":620667,"text":"And they're highly experienced, so they've done this"},{"time":622259,"text":"thousands and thousands of time."},{"time":623691,"text":"Obviously there's a big training effect, as you can imagine."},{"time":627928,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":629272,"text":"You can see they're very blasé and kind of effortless."},{"time":631207,"text":"Not only can they do it very well, they do it in a sort of lazy way."},{"time":635135,"text":"Right? Who thinks you could beat the chimps?"},{"time":638570,"text":"Wrong. (Laughter)"},{"time":640166,"text":"We can try. We'll try. Maybe we'll try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642604,"text":"Okay, so the next part of this study"},{"time":645194,"text":"I'm going to go quickly through"},{"time":646790,"text":"is based on an idea of Tetsuro Matsuzawa."},{"time":649482,"text":"He had a bold idea that -- what he called the cognitive trade-off hypothesis."},{"time":652511,"text":"We know chimps are faster and stronger."},{"time":653803,"text":"They're also very obsessed with status."},{"time":655483,"text":"His thought was, maybe they've preserved brain activities"},{"time":658439,"text":"and they practice them in development"},{"time":660607,"text":"that are really, really important to them"},{"time":662458,"text":"to negotiate status and to win,"},{"time":664668,"text":"which is something like strategic thinking during competition."},{"time":667666,"text":"So we're going to check that out"},{"time":669246,"text":"by having the chimps actually play a game"},{"time":671676,"text":"by touching two touch screens."},{"time":674314,"text":"The chimps are actually interacting with each other through the computers."},{"time":676754,"text":"They're going to press left or right."},{"time":678362,"text":"One chimp is called a matcher."},{"time":680475,"text":"They win if they press left, left,"},{"time":682458,"text":"like a seeker finding someone in hide-and-seek, or right, right."},{"time":685627,"text":"The mismatcher wants to mismatch."},{"time":686855,"text":"They want to press the opposite screen of the chimp."},{"time":689931,"text":"And the rewards are apple cube rewards."},{"time":692475,"text":"So here's how game theorists look at these data."},{"time":695003,"text":"This is a graph of the percentage of times"},{"time":696617,"text":"the matcher picked right on the x-axis,"},{"time":699235,"text":"and the percentage of times they predicted right"},{"time":700751,"text":"by the mismatcher on the y-axis."},{"time":703619,"text":"So a point here is the behavior by a pair of players,"},{"time":706819,"text":"one trying to match, one trying to mismatch."},{"time":709035,"text":"The NE square in the middle -- actually NE, CH and QRE --"},{"time":712315,"text":"those are three different theories of Nash equilibrium, and others,"},{"time":714771,"text":"tells you what the theory predicts,"},{"time":717195,"text":"which is that they should match 50-50,"},{"time":719467,"text":"because if you play left too much, for example,"},{"time":721635,"text":"I can exploit that if I'm the mismatcher by then playing right."},{"time":724351,"text":"And as you can see, the chimps, each chimp is one triangle,"},{"time":727115,"text":"are circled around, hovering around that prediction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730962,"text":"Now we move the payoffs."},{"time":732736,"text":"We're actually going to make the left, left payoff for the matcher a little bit higher."},{"time":736179,"text":"Now they get three apple cubes."},{"time":737699,"text":"Game theoretically, that should actually make the mismatcher's behavior shift,"},{"time":740499,"text":"because what happens is, the mismatcher will think,"},{"time":742089,"text":"oh, this guy's going to go for the big reward,"},{"time":743899,"text":"and so I'm going to go to the right, make sure he doesn't get it."},{"time":746964,"text":"And as you can see, their behavior moves up"},{"time":748629,"text":"in the direction of this change in the Nash equilibrium."},{"time":752077,"text":"Finally, we changed the payoffs one more time."},{"time":754391,"text":"Now it's four apple cubes,"},{"time":755583,"text":"and their behavior again moves towards the Nash equilibrium."},{"time":757755,"text":"It's sprinkled around, but if you average the chimps out,"},{"time":759790,"text":"they're really, really close, within .01."},{"time":761980,"text":"They're actually closer than any species we've observed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765179,"text":"What about humans? You think you're smarter than a chimpanzee?"},{"time":768372,"text":"Here's two human groups in green and blue."},{"time":771939,"text":"They're closer to 50-50. They're not responding to payoffs as closely,"},{"time":775683,"text":"and also if you study their learning in the game,"},{"time":777133,"text":"they aren't as sensitive to previous rewards."},{"time":779118,"text":"The chimps are playing better than the humans,"},{"time":780482,"text":"better in the sense of adhering to game theory."},{"time":782905,"text":"And these are two different groups of humans"},{"time":784324,"text":"from Japan and Africa. They replicate quite nicely."},{"time":787520,"text":"None of them are close to where the chimps are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790755,"text":"So here are some things we learned today."},{"time":792510,"text":"People seem to do a limited amount of strategic thinking"},{"time":794448,"text":"using theory of mind."},{"time":796259,"text":"We have some preliminary evidence from bargaining"},{"time":798176,"text":"that early warning signs in the brain might be used to predict"},{"time":800668,"text":"whether there will be a bad disagreement that costs money,"},{"time":802894,"text":"and chimps are better competitors than humans,"},{"time":804734,"text":"as judged by game theory."},{"time":807198,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":809055,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}